{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b00d35b4-15f5-42c2-82cc-c693556e2b05","content":"Here's a step-by-step approach to diagnose a hung .NET 8 app on Linux:\n\n**1. Identify the process:**\n```bash\nps aux | grep dotnet\n# or\npidof YourApp\n```\n\n**2. Capture a thread dump (non-destructive):**\n```bash\nkill -3 <PID>          # sends SIGQUIT, prints stack traces to stdout\n# or use dotnet-dump:\ndotnet-dump collect -p <PID>\ndotnet-dump analyze <dump-file>\n> clrstack -all\n```\n\n**3. Use `dotnet-trace` for live diagnostics:**\n```bash\ndotnet-trace collect -p <PID> --duration 00:00:30\n```\n\n**4. Check for deadlocks/threadpool starvation:**\n```bash\ndotnet-counters monitor -p <PID> --counters System.Runtime\n```\nLook at `ThreadPool Queue Length` and `ThreadPool Thread Count`.\n\n**5. Quick OS-level checks:**\n```bash\ntop -Hp <PID>          # per-thread CPU usage\nls /proc/<PID>/fd | wc -l   # file descriptor count\ncat /proc/<PID>/status       # memory, thread count\n```\n\n**Common causes:** deadlock, threadpool starvation (sync-over-async), exhausted connections/file descriptors, GC pause (rare for full hang), or waiting on an external dependency (DB, HTTP call).\n\nInstall the tools if needed: `dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump && dotnet tool install -g dotnet-counters`\n\nWould you like help interpreting specific output from any of these?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1341ba06-c2fd-4afb-8594-ff56b8a8211d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking for help diagnosing a hung .NET 8 application on a Linux VM. This is a troubleshooting/diagnostic question rather than a code change task. I'll provide concise guidance on how to diagnose a hung .NET application on Linux.","outputTokens":465,"requestId":"5018:2A473C:1E0D15:258A91:69F550AD"},"id":"b484099d-ddea-4a89-88f8-2337dc4f8773","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:17:45.146Z","parentId":"e6587414-da70-4591-92b6-5cf6a103275c"}
